casebody.data:
Percy A. ROBBINS and Keith Roberts, Appellants, v. CORDOVADA GOLD DREDGING CO., Appellee. No. 7677. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 7, 1935. Lyons & Orton and Ira D. Orton, all of Seattle, Wash., for appellants. William A. Gilmore, of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for the respective-parties, ordered appeal dismissed, without costs to either party; mandate forthwith.
